genresAdvancedInfo.name: cameroonian hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Cameroonian hip hop is a vibrant and energetic genre that has been gaining popularity in recent years. It is characterized by its use of African rhythms, traditional instruments, and socially conscious lyrics. Cameroonian hip hop artists often address issues such as poverty, corruption, and political oppression in their music, and are known for their dynamic live performances.
